    "After an initially moderate scrambling value (around 0.020 in the earliest layers), the index drops by roughly 60% and then remains in a narrow band near zero, eventually turning slightly negative.",
    "In this regime, global mixing provides little or even harmful benefit for reconstructing z 0, leading to predominantly local per-patch decisions.",
    "The model still achieves a nontrivial probe gain (+32.2%), but does not appear to coordinate sufficiently to reach a strong Neural Collapse geometry.",
    "ViT-B maintains controlled consensus.",
    "Its Scrambling Index stays in a low but consistently positive band (approximately 0.004 to 0.009), with a notable uptick during layers 7 to 9."
